The Lagos State Government, on Thursday, confirmed 51 new cases of coronavirus (COVID-19). The State Commissioner for Health, Prof. Akin Abayomi, disclosed this on his official Twitter page. This brings the total number of COVID-19 cases in Lagos State to 2,057. His tweet reads : “COVID19Lagos update as at 13th of May, 2020. “51 new #COVID19 Infection confirmed in Lagos. “Total number of confirmed #COVID19 cases in Lagos is now 2057 “26 fully recovered #COVID19Lagos patients; 13 females & 13 males; all Nigerians were discharged. “This brings the total number of #COVID19 discharged patients in Lagos to 528. “Together we can break the chain of #COVID19 transmission if we TakeResponsibility ForAGreaterLagos.”